              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+The Cache API provides an in-memory key-value cache implementation using a Map under the hood.\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates a new cache instance.\n+\n+```js\n+export function createCache() { }\n+```\n+\n+Returns an object with cache methods: `get`, `set`, `delete`, and `clear`.\n+\n+## Methods\n+\n+### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves the value associated with the specified key.\n+- **Parameters:** `key` - The key to look up.\n+- **Returns:** The cached value associated with the key, or `undefined` if not found.\n+\n+### set(key, value)\n+\n+Sets the specified key-value pair in the cache and returns the value.\n+- **Parameters:**\n+  - `key` - The key to store.\n+  - `value` - The value to associate with the key.\n+- **Returns:** The value that was set.\n+\n+### delete(key)\n+\n+Deletes the entry with the specified key from the cache.\n+- **Parameters:** `key` - The key to delete.\n+- **Returns:** `true` if the item was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n+\n+### clear()\n+\n+Removes all entries from the cache.\n+- **Returns:** `undefined`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n",
              "additions": 40,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
